data.name: Magi Runners
data.flavorText: It is said that a Magi once ran to the sun with these shoes on. You're not sure if you could, but they sure are fast.

data.name: Warlock's Slippers
data.flavorText: Many people don't trust Warlocks, so they don't get out much. These keep their feet cozy at home.

data.name: Crimson Boots
data.flavorText: These will certainly make a bold statement at your next wizarding get together.

data.name: Glacial Boots
data.flavorText: Extremely warm, these will keep your feet toasty in the mountains, but elsewhere they might make them sweaty.

data.name: Dragon Soles
data.flavorText: Are these dragonskin boots? Comfortable, but they smell a bit like burnt meat and old cave.

data.name: Hot Walkers
data.flavorText: Fitted with a handy self-drying flame, you can swim with these on and not have to worry.

data.name: Training Shoes
data.flavorText: Nothing special, but they'll protect your feet during training.

data.name: Light Shoes
data.flavorText: Lightweight and breathable they'll make your feet move faster and maybe a little less smelly.

data.name: Cloth Shoes
data.flavorText: Made from cloth, don't get them wet or your feet will be cold all day!

data.name: Heavy Shoes
data.flavorText: Whoa, these are heavy! Your feet feel pretty safe, but it also feels like you're walking through mud.

data.name: Leather Boots
data.flavorText: The choice of the everyday wizard. They say they're hand-crafted in the Spire.

data.name: Durofibre Boots
data.flavorText: Sleek, stylish and purple...

data.name: Magi-thread Boots
data.flavorText: You don't usually go for used boots, but the Magi made these long-lasting and really cool-looking.

data.name: Pyrium Boots
data.flavorText: You can wear these boots all year long, just make sure to change your wizard socks!

data.name: Mithril Boots
data.flavorText: Metal boots? You might not move that quickly, but your toes are totally protected!

data.name: Vitrium Boots
data.flavorText: When you wear them you move more gracefully but also always have the urge to dance.

data.name: Culix Boots
data.flavorText: Although Culix was a bit stuffy he had great taste in shoes.

data.name: Trialmaster's Boots
data.flavorText: Worn by a former master of trials, whose feet seemed to be quite small. They're a little snug.

data.name: Winter Boots
data.flavorText: Fuzzy on the inside and waterproof on the outside, the perfect choice for the long winter months.

data.name: Dragon Spike Boots
data.flavorText: Your friend wore these spiky boots to play wizard soccer once, they don't let him play anymore. I wonder why?

data.name: Warm Boots
data.flavorText: These sure do live up to their name.

data.name: Magic Boots
data.flavorText: You do feel suddenly more magical, but sometimes people laugh at the pointy toes.

data.name: Frost Saber Boots
data.flavorText: Made for battle in the cold, these shoes help you stay on top of the snow instead of sinking in.

data.name: Firefly Boots
data.flavorText: The trademark boots of the Firefly Forest. It says they're made with moss and lots of love.

data.name: Skywalkers
data.flavorText: A wizard once wanted to see how high he could jump with these shoes on. He's supposed to come back down any day now.

data.name: Duelist Boots
data.flavorText: Official boots of the Annual Wizard Dueling Contest, they say "The Choice of Champions" in big letters on their sides.

data.name: Shiverchill Boots
data.flavorText: Commonly worn by the tribes of the Shiverchill Mountains, many travellers take them when going to cold places.

data.name: Embers
data.flavorText: Made for wizards whose feet get cold. It feels like your toes are warming up in front of the fire.

data.name: Dire Pirate Boots
data.flavorText: Said to be suitable for dueling on rocky terrain.

data.name: Sea Sword Boots
data.flavorText: These boots cut through water, allowing wearers to walk as easily as if they were on land.

data.name: Bubble Boots
data.flavorText: These bubbly boots make you feel like you could float through the air.

data.name: Admiral's Boots
data.flavorText: These boots have been through many adventures on the high seas, but they're still sturdy!

data.name: Shell Armor Boots
data.flavorText: These boots are so tough, they make your toes smell like the ocean!

data.name: Magma Boots
data.flavorText: Keep your toes warm with these lava rockin' boots inspired by Magmischief himself.

data.name: Skates of Glory
data.flavorText: These skates are so much better than sneakers when you are out on the ice. So sit down, lace up, and go skate!

data.name: Emerald Elf Booties
data.flavorText: Walk in these elfin shoes and it feels like you are walking barefoot through a field of fragrant flowers.

data.name: Fire Walkers
data.flavorText: CLUNK! CLUNK! CLUNK! Use these heavy boots to walk in the deepest lava.

data.name: Retro Rocket Boots
data.flavorText: These boots will allow you to walk on the moon, just don't expect to move too fast.

data.name: Gyro Leg Extend-O's
data.flavorText: As one of the latest innovations in Skywatch technology, the Gyro Leg Extend-O's have gathered a lot of attention from other towns for their outstanding performance.

data.name: Flying Feet Boots
data.flavorText: Fly around the world in these boots and become the ultimate explorer!

data.name: Spartan Greaves
data.flavorText: The ultimate protection for a seasoned wizard. With bronze from knee to toe, you're all covered.

data.name: Titan Hunter Boots
data.flavorText: Finely crafted footwear decorated with dazzling Titan Shards. Only the Floatlings know how to use these Shards to create mighty wizard gear.

data.name: Ninja Covers
data.flavorText: These ninja covers will make you move like the wind.

data.name: Beastmaster Boots
data.flavorText: To be a Beastmaster, one must walk in the footsteps of a beast.

data.name: Red Knight Greaves
data.flavorText: Forged using the strongest and lightest of metals.

data.name: Viking Shoes
data.flavorText: Traveling great distances puts a toll on anyone's feet. These leather shoes are said to last a very, very long time.

data.name: Raider Boots
data.flavorText: Flexible boots that allow the wearer to make quick and sudden movements.

data.name: Black Knight Greaves
data.flavorText: Sturdy, shiny, and very mysterious. Everything you need to be considered a Black Knight.

data.name: Boots of the Harpooner
data.flavorText: Watertight and sure footed to ensure perfect balance with every throw.

data.name: Soles of the Spy
data.flavorText: These fancy dress shoes contain loss-lace comm links to Spy HQ.

data.name: Tech Wizard Runners
data.flavorText: Hi-tech shoes of the future. Of course they light up!

data.name: Archivist Boots
data.flavorText: Show off your skills as a true Archivist with these Archivist boots!

data.name: Astral Boots
data.flavorText: These boots were worn by those few wizards who mastered the rare Astral magic.

data.name: Academy Uniform Shoes
data.flavorText: Match that hat and uniform with the perfect pair of Academy-issued shoes.

data.name: Monster Riders
data.flavorText: These boots are worn by those who have learned to ride winged beasts of any size!

data.name: Crystal Boots
data.flavorText: You won't have to worry about stubbing your toes with these crystal-toed boots.

data.name: Triceratops Greaves
data.flavorText: No wizard will want to step on your toes while you're wearing these spikes.

data.name: Leaf Booties
data.flavorText: These shoes have been said to grant the user the ability to be as light as a leaf!

data.name: Titan Brawler Greaves
data.flavorText: Harvey mixed metal with Titan shards to create stronger boots that can't even get scratched.

data.name: Swift Boots
data.flavorText: Soft and silent, perfect for a rogue looking to avoid attention.

data.name: Alpine Cleats
data.flavorText: Stay grounded in slippery situations with these spiked climbing shoes.

data.name: Blizzard Boots
data.flavorText: These boots leave creature-like prints in the snow.

data.name: Prospector Work Boots
data.flavorText: These keep a miner's feet dry when stumbling across underground rivers and waterfalls.

data.name: Ruin Explorer Boots
data.flavorText: These are some heavy-duty explorer boots. They even have pockets!

data.name: Storm Titan Boots
data.flavorText: They might look heavy, but cloudy softness fills these stylish boots. What's more, they crackle like thunder with every step!

data.name: Ruin Dweller Boots
data.flavorText: Strangely, you can feel the ground with your feet when you wear these shoes. They help you grow closer to nature.

data.name: Rubber Ducky Boots
data.flavorText: These boots will really quack you up. Sold during Summerfest.

data.name: Trekking Boots
data.flavorText: Ward off angry monsters AND stay incredibly warm. Perfect for long treks in Shiverchill Mountains.

data.name: 1x Conjure Cube
data.flavorText: A bundle of one conjure cube.

data.name: 5x Conjure Cube
data.flavorText: A bundle of five conjure cubes.

data.name: 20x Conjure Cube
data.flavorText: A bundle of twenty conjure cubes.

data.name: Gold
data.flavorText: The gold standard for shopping. Earn these from quests, battles, and more!

data.name: Candy Corn
data.flavorText: The primary currency of Pumpkinfest. Used to buy costumes and cool items in the town square during the event!

data.name: Copper Coin
data.flavorText: A rusty old coin. Used to buy rare artifacts from the wandering merchant.

data.name: Star Shards
data.flavorText: The primary currency of the Starlight Festival. These are used to buy costumes and cool items in the town square during the event!

data.name: Magic Snowflakes
data.flavorText: The primary currency of Winterfest. These are used to buy costumes and cool items in the town square during the event!

data.name: Wood
data.flavorText: This special wood was used by Floatlings to construct makeshift houses as they traveled around the island in search of knowledge.

data.name: Dragon Flies
data.flavorText: These captured Dragon Flies can be traded to Mama Star for special dragon-ish items.

data.name: Titan Shards
data.flavorText: Shards broken off of a Titan created by the Order of Influence. Can be given to a Floatling to have the Shadow magic removed from it, in exchange for rare items.

data.name: Hot-Hots
data.flavorText: Adventure in Bonfire Spire to earn these lava chips, then spend them at the Hot Hot Threads shop.

data.name: Florans
data.flavorText: Adventure in Firefly Forest to earn these woodland coins, then spend them at the Firefly Outfitters shop.

data.name: Yars
data.flavorText: Adventure in Shipwreck Shores to earn these pirate coins, then spend them at the Ocean Outfitters shop.

data.name: Shivers
data.flavorText: Adventure in Shiverchill Mountains to earn these icy coins, then spend them at the Snowday Sales shop.

data.name: Aeros
data.flavorText: Adventure in Skywatch to earn these mechanical coins, then spend them at the Sky-High Values shop.

data.name: Magic Eggs
data.flavorText: These magical eggs are only found when the Springfest is active. They can be collected by adventuring or performing Springfest activities. Spend them at the Fox or Bunny shops.

data.name: Golden Pages
data.flavorText: The primary currency of the Academy Archives. Five of these are collected per Archive run to summon a prize!

data.name: Academy Pages
data.flavorText: Adventure through the Academy's Archives to collect these pages, then exchange them at the Academy's shop.

data.name: Sand Dollars

data.name: Gecko
data.flavorText: A gecko can climb almost any surface and even upside down! This gecko seems to be afraid of heights, though. Can be bought at the Pet Shop in Lamplight Town.

data.name: Leopard Gecko
data.flavorText: A gecko can climb almost any surface and even upside down! This gecko seems to be afraid of heights, though. Can be bought at the Pet Shop in Lamplight Town.

data.name: Turtle
data.flavorText: Turtles are normally pretty slow, but this one has no issue keeping up with you! Can be bought at the Pet Shop in Lamplight Town.

data.name: Baby Reindeer
data.flavorText: These happy little creatures couldn't possibly be more excited to join you on your quest! They are well known for being great pals on adventures. Sold during Winterfest.

data.name: Penguin
data.flavorText: What's black and white and chilly all over? Why a penguin of course! This polar pal is ready to explore beyond the cold lands it calls home with you! Sold during Winterfest.

data.name: Baby Snowman
data.flavorText: With just a little bit of magic, this snowman came to life, and now, he's looking for a buddy to explore with! Don't worry, he can't melt! Sold during Winterfest.

data.name: Saber-Tooth Cat
data.flavorText: This furry friend loves to frolic in the snow and play hide and seek in the caverns deep within Shiverchill Mountains.

data.name: Purple Owl
data.flavorText: Shiverchill is home to many interesting creatures. The rare Purple Owl is one of them! Some say that these owls have magical powers.

data.name: Steam-Powered Robot Bird 9001
data.flavorText: Steam-powered robot birds were created to help workers in Skywatch repair the weather machines.

data.name: Flower Turtle
data.flavorText: Some turtles that live in Firefly Forest fall asleep in soil for long periods of time. When this happens, flowers begin to grow on their shell!

data.name: Rainbow Panda
data.flavorText: The rainbow panda is so hard to find in the forest, because it can blend in so well with its environment.

data.name: Cloud Sheep
data.flavorText: These sheep like to get around by riding on gusts of wind that sweep them up. If you ever see a group of them gathered together, watch out! Their fur can rub together and create lightning storms!

data.name: Cuddly Cactus
data.flavorText: This cactus is surprisingly cuddly! The needles on it fall off at a very young age, leaving its soft skin free to cuddle!

data.name: Flame Salamander
data.flavorText: These little fiery friends scamper, scurry, and swim through the lava of Bonfire Spire. Because of this, very few people have ever seen one!

data.name: Fox
data.flavorText: A sly fox would usually keep its distance, but this one is happy to follow you anywhere! Reward for linking your account with your parent's account.

data.name: Sparkle Hamster
data.flavorText: A sparkly, pocket-sized friend who loves to stuff lots of food in its cheeks!

data.name: Sparkle Kitty
data.flavorText: A sparkly kitty whose glittering fur will be the talk of the town!

data.name: Sparkle Puppy
data.flavorText: This sparkly best friend is loyal to the end and is happy to follow you anywhere!

data.name: Big Hex
data.flavorText: He comes from an unknown place with an unknown name. You've decided to call him Big Hex for the large bolts that seem to hold him together.

data.name: Florafox
data.flavorText: Florafox can speak with nearby plants and trees by planting itself in the soil. The bulb on Florafox's tail produces a pollen that can heal any plant, no matter how injured or withered.

data.name: Arctursus
data.flavorText: The air around Arctursus is always cold. This is because the tips of his fur are made from an ice that can never melt, and so no matter where he goes he is always at a comfortable temperature.

data.name: Diveodile
data.flavorText: Diveodile's natural magic ability is boosted by the Warden pendant it wears, allowing it to cast strong water spells to generate water, or even control the water around itself!

data.name: Magmischief
data.flavorText: While traveling underground, Magmischief can sense movement on the surface, so he knows exactly where to appear and get the biggest scare out of those who have entered Bonfire Spire.

data.name: Crab
data.flavorText: What a cute little crab! He blows bubbles too! Pinch pinch pop!

data.name: Baby Squid
data.flavorText: What's more adorable than a baby squid that squirts ink? Not much!

data.name: Puffer Fish
data.flavorText: This floaty fish is fun to have bob along behind you.

data.name: Cat Fish
data.flavorText: It's a cat AND a fish! What's not to love?!

data.name: Chill & Char
data.flavorText: Chill & Char are best friends, not just because they share a body, but because their abilities complement each other so well.

data.name: Tidus
data.flavorText: Tidus can create massive waves with a flap of his powerful wings below water. Tidus has also been known to do it just to ride the waves.

data.name: Luma
data.flavorText: On sunny days, Luma loves to romp through flower-filled fields, soaking up the sun rays.

data.name: Eclipse
data.flavorText: Eclipse soars and swoops through the clouds in the night sky, playing hide-and-go-seek with the moon and stars.

data.name: Fancy Ferret
data.flavorText: These speedy little fellows can be pretty sneaky. Watch out, they may even try to hide your things!

data.name: Smelly the Skunk
data.flavorText: Woah! What's that funky smell? It wasn't me.

data.name: Hot Shot Monsta
data.flavorText: These guys love to play in lava and pop the lava bubbles.

data.name: Pyro Peck
data.flavorText: Who needs a campfire when you have your own Pyro Peck to keep you warm and cozy!

data.name: Robota Monsta
data.flavorText: Even robots can have hearts. Love your Robota Monsta and this little monster will love you back!

data.name: Cloudstrider
data.flavorText: Cloudstriders were once used as Skywatch's sky watch, patrolling between the clouds. Now you can adopt one as your own. You will feel safer right away.

data.name: Supachill Monsta
data.flavorText: Supachill Monstas are super chill and super fun to be around! They can't wait to go on new and exciting adventures.

data.name: Snow Ermine
data.flavorText: Supachill Monstas are super chill and super fun to be around! They can't wait to go on new and exciting adventures.

data.name: Peak Peck
data.flavorText: Peak Pecks will absolutely love you as long as you feed them icicles every once in a while.

data.name: Fox Battle Buddy
data.flavorText: Bring the spirit of the Fox with you everywhere with this brave battle buddy.

data.name: Bunny Bandit Buddy
data.flavorText: The Bunny Bandit Buddy is your constant companion, always hopping a few steps behind you.

data.name: Baby Rex
data.flavorText: This playful little dinosaur will happily follow you everywhere, bobbing its tiny little arms and big head.

data.name: Flying Piggy
data.flavorText: It turns out that piggies really can fly!

data.name: Timberwolf
data.flavorText: This mysterious looking wolf offers protection and love for its owner.

data.name: Puffin
data.flavorText: This friendly bird loves being around water. Puffins can splash around all day!

data.name: Mini Spybot
data.flavorText: He always has your back, and never leaves old batteries on the sidewalk.

data.name: Drone
data.flavorText: This Drone has so much energy! Who knew they could make such fun buddies?

data.name: Glow-worm
data.flavorText: Often found around books in the Archives, these little glow-worms love to read anything they can inch their way to!

data.name: Enchanted Book
data.flavorText: Why carry your spell book when you can have it follow you?

data.name: Snowy Owl
data.flavorText: The traditional wizard sidekick, complete the look of your Academy uniform with the official Academy pet.

data.name: Cat-o'-Lantern
data.flavorText: No matter where you go, this kitty will follow you with a glow!

data.name: Spooky
data.flavorText: What's so scary about a floating marshmallow?

data.name: Crystal Muncher
data.flavorText: There is no other creature that enjoys eating crystals as much as the crystal muncher.

data.name: Baby Triceratops
data.flavorText: It may be a baby but it sure can pack a powerful headbutt!

data.name: Robo-Pup
data.flavorText: Robo-Pup is just like a normal puppy, except with super-speedy rocket paws.

data.name: Snake
data.flavorText: This lil guy slithers around from place to place and smells things with his tiny little tongue.

data.name: Chirpy Birdie
data.flavorText: Hopping her way around - she sure loves to meet other pets. Gifted from a Membership Box.

data.name: Speedy Turtle
data.flavorText: Mr. Turtle wasn't going to take being called slow anymore - an upgrade to wheels now has him zipping across the island! Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Blurb
data.flavorText: An alien buddy following you around and ready to zap at the next wizard who would attack you. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Ursa Minor
data.flavorText: This cuddly little bear shines just as brightly as the stars in the sky! Sold during the Starlight Festival.

data.name: Sharky
data.flavorText: Stop, sharky time! Obtained during Summerfest.

data.name: Snow Puppy
data.flavorText: This lil' pup is made of snow and will happily follow you wherever you go! Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Lucky Rat
data.flavorText: This unique little rat has been said to bring good luck to the wizards it follows. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Festive Puppy
data.flavorText: This little pup is always in a festive mood. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Nessie
data.flavorText: Though Nessie prefers the water, it'll happily swim in the air and follow you for treats. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Snup
data.flavorText: These odd-looking fluffs have often been spotted slinking around Shiverchill Mountains. What's Snup with that?

data.name: Plump Snup
data.flavorText: What's a Snup? Not much, what's Snup with you?

data.name: Sparkle Snup
data.flavorText: Shine bright like a Snup.

data.name: Flamingo
data.flavorText: Fun Flamingo Fact: A flock of flamingos is called a flamboyance!

data.name: Ruin Bat
data.flavorText: Bats like to live on Harmony Island in large groups, but this one seems to want to go on adventures with you.

data.name: Spider
data.flavorText: This little spider likes to spend its free time browsing the web.

data.name: Pumpki-bat
data.flavorText: It's a bit strange for a gourd to be flying, but this squash sure seems pumped about it.

data.name: Moose
data.flavorText: The 'bell' is the flap of skin beneath each moose's throat, though it doesn't chime. Sold during Winterfest.

data.name: Snowy Flake
data.flavorText: Despite being called 'Snowy', this little buddy seems to be made of ice rather than snow. Sold during Winterfest.

data.name: Lucky Ox
data.flavorText: This mini ox is supposed to bring good luck to whatever wizard it follows. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Benny Bunny
data.flavorText: You'll feel like you're hopping through adventures with Benny Bunny by your side! Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Crocodile
data.flavorText: Don't try to wear this croc on your foot! Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Ruin Rabbit
data.flavorText: This is a unique type of rabbit that can only be found on Harmony Island.

data.name: Tasmanian Tiger
data.flavorText: What a mysterious animal. It looks like a mix between a tiger, a dog, and a kangaroo! You can find them on Harmony Island.

data.name: Hedgehog
data.flavorText:
This cute and spiky buddy likes to relax on his back. 

Don't let let his stubby legs fool you, this hedgehog gains great speed when it rolls with you.

data.name: Slippery Penguin
data.flavorText: This Penguin knows how to have fun! It will slip and slide on its stomach beside you, leaving a cool trail of snowflakes behind.

data.name: Kitten Trio
data.flavorText: These kittens are inseparable and are not really fond of strangers. If they don't run away that means they really like you.

data.name: Camouflage Chameleon
data.flavorText: This buddy loves to try to blend into its environment. If you're able to see when it changes colours this means the chameleon really trusts you.

data.name: Rainbow Butterfly
data.flavorText: This buddy loves to fly in the air. Legend says it sprinkles magic particles on their friends for good luck and fortune.

data.name: Cool Mane Lion
data.flavorText: This cool lion takes pride in being around cool people. So if stays by your side you must be cool too.

data.name: Dolphin
data.flavorText: Your friends will flipper when they see this cute Dolphin! Sold during Summerfest.

data.name: Bumblebee
data.flavorText: A cute, fuzzy Bumblebee to call your own! Sold during Summerfest.

data.name: Arctic Fox
data.flavorText: This sly creature can be found exploring the Ice Tower.

data.name: Terrosaur Bone
data.flavorText: This bone looks like a piece from a much larger skeleton. I better find them all!

data.flavorText: It appears to be a large beetle, preserved in a piece of amber. Neat!

data.name: Trellobyte
data.flavorText: Trellobytes once scavenged the ocean floors, looking for scraps and collectible cards.

data.name: Sharp Claw
data.flavorText: A large claw to some carnivore...or perhaps an ill-tempered herbivore.

data.name: Dragonfly in Amber
data.flavorText: This dragonfly must have landed on a tree, and got caught in some tree sap.

data.flavorText: This hat happens to have its own personality, so make sure you wash your hair regularly!

data.name: E-nigma
data.flavorText: Question me this, question me that...how good will you look, wearing this hat?

data.name: Highlord's Crown
data.flavorText: An ancient ruler passed this crown down to his children, and now it's in your hands.

data.name: Hound's Helm
data.flavorText: The Hound's Helm only looks like a dog...in fact, it was actually made by dogs!

data.name: Winged Helm
data.flavorText: This Helm was found in the ruins of an ancient city, but mysteriously disappeared...

data.name: Mayhem's Guise
data.flavorText: Mayhem was a warlock that caused lots of trouble. He was so well known that he used to wear this hat to hide among the crowds.

data.name: Frozen Crown
data.flavorText: This crown belonged to the terrible Ice King but he gave it away when a witch turned him into a nice king.

data.name: Infernal Helm
data.flavorText: The feathers tickle a little bit but this hat sure seems to spook your opponents. Maybe it's because it's still alive!

data.name: Training Cap
data.flavorText: Keeps your head out of the sun and your hair dry during those tough training days.

data.name: Light Hat
data.flavorText: It fits so nicely, and doesn't give you a case of nasty wizarding hat hair.

data.name: Cloth Hat
data.flavorText: It's cloth. It's green. It's a green, cloth hat!

data.name: Heavy Hat
data.flavorText: Someone told you that this was a Platypus that was turned into a hat. You're not sure, but it does seem water-resistant.

data.name: Leather Hat
data.flavorText: Leather hats are all the rage these days, especially since Worly the Wonderful wears one.

data.name: Durofibre Hat
data.flavorText: In classic wizarding blue, you might think this hat old-fashioned, but the old wizards smile when you wear it.

data.name: Magi-thread Hat
data.flavorText: The Magi loved the sun most of all, they just didn't like it burning their heads. So they made this popular hat.

data.name: Pyrium Hat
data.flavorText: Made with Pyrium thread in a classic style. This hat is a good option just about everywhere!

data.name: Mithril Hat
data.flavorText: Some think that the mithril in this hat gives you psychic powers, but who knows? Maybe you, when you're wearing it.

data.name: Vitrium Hat
data.flavorText: Older wizards don't like how younger ones wear this hat backwards.

data.name: Culix Hat
data.flavorText: Worn by fans of Culix, the famous historian who wrote "101 wacky warlock wands" and "The Tales of Hapless Headless Heath".

data.name: Trialmaster's Circlet
data.flavorText: This ceremonial circlet is exceedingly rare and grants wisdom to those who wear it. Who would give it up?

data.name: Winterfest Hat
data.flavorText: The official hat worn by helpers at Winterfest!

data.name: Winter Hat
data.flavorText: It may look like just a winter hat, but it is actually a MAGICAL winter hat!

data.name: Fancy Tophat
data.flavorText: This stylish hat is intended to be worn at formal gatherings, but you can wear it anywhere you want.

data.name: Earmuffs
data.flavorText: Need to keep your ears warm, but your hair neat? Try these earmuffs on!

data.name: Parka Hood
data.flavorText: Mrrrrrf mmmrrrhhmhhh mhhhmhmhr!

data.name: Reindeer Antlers
data.flavorText: If you've ever needed to look like a reindeer, this is the hat for you!

data.name: Snowman Head
data.flavorText: A large snowman mask, and it's even made out of snow! Brrrr!

data.name: Dragon Helm
data.flavorText: Legend says that those who wear can hear the songs of dragons. Often its wearers can be heard singing to themselves.

data.name: Frost Saber Cap
data.flavorText: When they grow into adults, Frost Saber Cats choose a new form. This one chose to be a hat for some reason.

data.name: Firefly Hat
data.flavorText: A magical hat crafted by the magical creatures in Firefly Forest.

data.name: Dragon Tiara
data.flavorText: Some say that if the correct words are spoken, this tiara will spit flames. Be careful what you say while wearing it!

data.name: Dragon Spike Crown
data.flavorText: Formerly worn by Eustace Redhale "The King of Dragons" and the last ruler to ride one. It has the power of dragon's fire.

data.name: Duelist Helm
data.flavorText: The hat of one of the greatest wizards in the Academy.

data.name: Shiverchill Hat
data.flavorText: The Shiverchill Tribes wear this hat during important ceremonies like the "Welcome to Winter" and "Tobogganing Tuesdays".

data.name: Tinder Toque
data.flavorText: A celebratory hat worn by the people of Spire on feast days. You can store a lot of food in it if you're sneaky.

data.name: Captain's Hat
data.flavorText: The choice of pirate captains everywhere! It smells like the sea and comes with a cool-looking eye patch!

data.name: Bandana
data.flavorText: The favorite head gear of scurvy dogs because it's very absorbent and pirates love polka dots.

data.name: Skycap
data.flavorText: This is the hat worn by the Skyfolk - the small creatures who live in the clouds above the Academy.

data.name: Mira's Hood
data.flavorText: Mira's hood radiates a powerful energy...

data.name: Desert Hat
data.flavorText: A fashionable hat worn by initiates in the Oasis Institute of Natural Creatures (OINC).

data.name: Explorer Hat
data.flavorText: This hat is rumored to have been worn by Looter Dan, the Academy's greatest explorer.

data.name: Tinkerer Hat
data.flavorText: An old hat, probably worn by the people who built the ancient city.

data.name: Robot Mask
data.flavorText: You aren't a robot, but this hat sure makes you look like one!

data.name: TEK-Y4 Headphones
data.flavorText: These headphones are used to enhance the dancing skills of the TEK-Y4 dancing robots!

data.name: Pumpkinhead
data.flavorText: This actually smells like a pumpkin! Kind of sweaty, though.

data.name: Luminite Mask
data.flavorText: A plastic Luminite mask...pretty well-made, I think!

data.name: Specter Hood
data.flavorText: The hood of a creepy specter - a bit dingy, but that just makes it even creepier.

data.name: Franky Mask
data.flavorText: A plastic mask of Franky the Stein, the popular TV monster.

data.name: Skelly Mask
data.flavorText: A plastic mask of a skelly.

data.name: Wolfy Mask
data.flavorText: A plastic wolf mask... ooooo scary!

data.name: Climber's Toque
data.flavorText: A thick, durable knitted toque, perfect for braving the harsh mountain conditions.

data.name: Featherwing Helm
data.flavorText: A standard viking helmet, but with wings! Who cares if they don't make you fly, they're wings!

data.name: Frost Beard's Mug
data.flavorText: The helm of the great Frost Beard. Causes the wearer to grow a beard of ice.

data.name: Lady Yeti Mask
data.flavorText: A Yeti mask covered in makeup...

data.name: Male Yeti Mask
data.flavorText: A Yeti mask...so scary!

data.name: Red Helm
data.flavorText: This relic from a more technical age seems to be restored perfectly...it even has that new car smell!

data.name: Ghastly Hood
data.flavorText: A strange feeling overwhelms you when you put on this hood; it makes you feel...mysterious.

data.name: Draconyx Helm
data.flavorText: This helm was worn by the warrior wizards of legend - meant only for those who passed the toughest of tests.

data.name: Black Fang
data.flavorText: This helm is worn only by the greatest of Bounty Hunters. Its staring gaze strikes fear into the hearts of all who see it!

data.name: Hunter Hat
data.flavorText: The standard-issue hat of a Bounty Hunter. It is durable enough to wear in a storm and provides excellent visibility.

data.name: Bee Hat
data.flavorText: The hat from a bee costume. It smells faintly of flowers.

data.name: Candle Knight Helm
data.flavorText: The magical flame on this helmet can never be extinguished.

data.name: Big Hex Helmet
data.flavorText: A helmet crafted by Big Hex's creator, the Warden who studied in Skywatch.

data.name: Arctursus Hood
data.flavorText: If Arctursus ever found someone lost in the mountains, he would shed some ice fur and create this hood out of it to keep them warm.

data.name: Florafox Bonnet
data.flavorText: This bonnet was grown in a Warden's garden in Firefly Forest.

data.name: Diveodile Toque
data.flavorText: Townsfolk that live on the shore crafted this diving toque in honor of the sea guardian Diveodile.

data.name: Magmischief Helm
data.flavorText: This helmet was crafted out of cooled lava from Bonfire Spire.

data.name: Cactus Cranium
data.flavorText: Perfect for your prickly personality. Poke! Poke!! Poke!!!

data.name: Chicken Hood
data.flavorText: This hood is no yolk! It is said that it was once worn by the bravest of warriors!

data.name: Petal Helm
data.flavorText: It's a special springtime hat!

data.name: Snowflake Hairclip
data.flavorText: A snowflake fell from the skies and landed on your head. At least, that's what you can tell everyone.

data.name: Weather Helmet
data.flavorText: Whatever the weather, this hat's got you covered!

data.name: Dire Pirate Mask
data.flavorText: Great for adventure on the high seas!

data.name: Jelly Cap
data.flavorText: Ceremonial hat inspired by magical jellyfish.

data.name: Deep Diving Helmet
data.flavorText: It's so old that it won't help you breathe underwater anymore, but it's still sturdy.

data.name: Sea Sword Cap
data.flavorText: This sleek hat will make you look sharp as a shark's fin!

data.name: Admiral's Cappello
data.flavorText: This old hat belonged to the admiral who led the charge against the evil Order of Influence many years ago.

data.name: Shell Armor Helmet
data.flavorText: This sturdy helmet has been forged under the pressure of deep ocean water.

data.name: Mushroom Cap
data.flavorText: Wearing this will make you look like a fun girl or a fun guy!

data.name: Wood Knight Helm
data.flavorText: The brim of this helmet is made from a hard-to-find nut that grows deep within Firefly Forest.

data.name: Polar Knight Helm
data.flavorText: Helm forged from ice found at the top of Shiverchill Mountain.

data.name: Wing Guard Ushanka
data.flavorText: The Wing Guard patrolled the skies to protect the machinery of Skywatch from people trying to mess with the weather. That is, until the Puppet Master appeared.

data.name: Chef's Hat
data.flavorText: This surprisingly soft hat will keep you cool in the kitchen.

data.name: Goblin Mask
data.flavorText: This goofy goblin mask is a favorite costume among young wizards during Pumpkinfest.

data.name: Scarecrow Mask
data.flavorText: Don't be scared! Unless you're a crow, that is!

data.name: Mummy Mask
data.flavorText: This classic Pumpkinfest look is sure to spook your friends!

data.name: Fallen Leaf Mask
data.flavorText: Celebrate the fall colors, or just hide in a pile of leaves.

data.name: Helm of the Glaring Dragon
data.flavorText: The fierce gaze of dragons protects you.

data.name: Dragon Command Circlet
data.flavorText: Feel as commanding as a dragon, or just say you are a dragoncorn.

data.name: Ice Dragon Tooth Crown
data.flavorText: This rare crown is formed from Ice Dragon teeth, giving you extra combat power!

data.name: Tidus Armor Cap
data.flavorText: The ultimate cap for wavy hair, from Tidus, prince of the waves!

data.name: Chill Char Helmet
data.flavorText: The two heads of Chill & Char combined into one helmet. Now you can look both Cool and Hot at the same time!

data.name: Luma Helmet
data.flavorText: The radiance of the sun shines from your head with this helmet inspired by Luma and her love of the sun.

data.name: Eclipse Helmet
data.flavorText: This helm was made from scales that Eclipse shed a long time ago, and adorned with his moon symbol.

data.name: Sky Captain Cap
data.flavorText: Full steam ahead! Command the skies with this time tracking captain's cap.

data.name: Flowers and Sprockets
data.flavorText: Gear up with bright flowers and shiny brass fittings. Practical and pretty!

data.name: Blue Star Helm
data.flavorText: Bee Bah Boo! Go Team Blue!

data.name: Red Badge Helm
data.flavorText: Protect your head! Go Team Red!

data.name: Ice Crystal Ski Cap
data.flavorText: The warmest hat in the land, with the hottest fashion. Perfect for sipping cocoa on a mountaintop. Part of the elite Ice Crystal set.

data.name: Snowy Snow Hat
data.flavorText: Brrr--is it snowing? Bring the cold weather with you wherever you go.

data.name: Hit by Snowball Hat
data.flavorText: Nothing says "Hey, who threw that?" better than this big snowball hat.

data.name: Titan Power Helm
data.flavorText: Crafted from repurposed Titan Shards. The Floatlings plant the Shards in the ground, and after sprinkling them with Astral magic, remove the Shadow Magic from them.

data.name: Glacier Helm
data.flavorText: The only thing harder than your head is this helmet formed from the crystal ice mined from deep in the heart of a glacier.

data.name: Tres Cool Ski Hat
data.flavorText: Bring the winter chill with this cool knit cap and visor combo.

data.name: Nice Holiday Bow
data.flavorText: A festive holiday ribbon that is just for the fun of it.

data.name: Fancy Holiday Bow
data.flavorText: Show your holiday spirit with this amazing topper. It's 'knot' to be missed!

data.name: Deluxe Holiday Bow
data.flavorText: It's top quality! Bow to no one with this amazing rare holiday hat!

data.name: Red Riding Hood
data.flavorText: A lovely, eye-catching hood that will surely scare away monsters with its bright red colour.

data.name: Emerald Elf Cap
data.flavorText: This swirly cap was specially crafted by the Elves of Firefly Forest to be worn by nobles.

data.name: Elf Power Tiara
data.flavorText: A headpiece passed down to the wizards who have shown great kindness and loyalty for their comrades.

data.name: Fire Feather Headdress
data.flavorText: A ceremonial hat sewn with magic in every thread to ward away evil spirits.

data.name: Hungry Spirit Mask
data.flavorText: The spirit living in this mask is ALWAYS hungry. Don't worry though, it won't try to eat you.

data.name: Flora Tropica Headband
data.flavorText: This headband is very popular among the dancers of Bonfire Spire. They say that the decorative flowers can only be found at the peak of the volcano.

data.name: Retro Rocket Helmet
data.flavorText: This sturdy helmet was created by the engineers of Skywatch to allow wizards to explore space.

data.name: Arc Welder Helmet
data.flavorText: Just try to break through this tough plate of metal. Good luck putting it on, though. Part of the Arc Welder set.

data.name: Spartan Helmet
data.flavorText: A sturdy bronze helmet with a brightly colored brush to top it all off.

data.name: Titan Hunter Antlers
data.flavorText: Crafted from repurposed Titan Shards. The Floatlings plant the Shards in the ground, and after sprinkling them with Astral magic, remove the Shadow Magic from them.

data.name: Fox Faction Mask
data.flavorText: Support the Foxes! Wear this or any other Fox faction hat to get into the Fox camp.

data.name: Fox Squire Helm
data.flavorText: The standard helmet worn by the junior Fox Knights. Wag your fox tail with bravery and honor.

data.name: Fox Knight Helm
data.flavorText: Never run, never surrender with this elite war helm worn by the top knights of the Fox faction.

data.name: Bunny Bandit Mask
data.flavorText: Support the Bunnies! Wear this or any other Bunny faction hat to get into the secret Bunny camp.

data.name: Bunny Scout Cap
data.flavorText: The standard cap worn by the junior Bunny Bandits. Be quick, be smart, be Bunny!

data.name: Bunny Ranger Cap
data.flavorText: The elite Bunny Rangers hear every rustle in the forest with the big ears on this dashing green cap.

data.name: Mystic Member Hat
data.flavorText: This is a magical wizard hat crafted specially for Members. There is no other hat like it.

data.name: Panda Hood
data.flavorText: Now is your chance to become a panda yourself!

data.name: Baby Rex Hood
data.flavorText: ROAR! I'm a dinosaur!

data.name: Ninja Hood
data.flavorText: The perfect disguise for an explorer. No one will know that it's you.

data.name: Beastmaster Hood
data.flavorText: A well crafted hood and a Beastmaster's treasured item. Are you a wizard or a beast?

data.name: Red Knight Helmet
data.flavorText: This helmet represents a Knight's loyalty and gives them courage.

data.name: Viking Horns
data.flavorText: The band of wizards who wore this helmet chose to put giant horns on both sides to make them stand out.

data.name: Raider Helmet
data.flavorText: A helmet that offers great protection from all angles. The spikes are mostly for decoration.

data.name: Sunglasses
data.flavorText: Wear the gaze with the daze...

data.name: Cat Ears
data.flavorText: Be cute as a kitty, AND be able to hear a mouse from a mile away...

data.name: Black Knight Helm
data.flavorText: This durable helm offers great protection and makes you look twice as cool.

data.name: Catch of the Harpooner
data.flavorText: Something smells fishy... Would you look at that, there's a fish on my head!

data.name: Shades of the Spy
data.flavorText: These glasses have X-ray vision and danger sensing. Wear them at all times.

data.name: Noot's Cap
data.flavorText: Noot's very own cap! Smells a bit funky...

data.name: Tech Wizard Lens
data.flavorText: Who needs glasses when you have one of these? Technology sure is amazing.

data.name: Archivist Hat
data.flavorText: Show off your skills as a true Archivist with this Archivist hat!

data.name: Astral Hood
data.flavorText: This hood was worn by those few wizards who mastered the rare Astral magic.

data.name: Academy Hat
data.flavorText: The Academy's official hat for students, it's key for looking the part of a wizard in training!

data.name: Frog Wizard Hood
data.flavorText: Ribbit? Ribbit Ribbit Ribbit Ribbit Ribbit Ribbit

data.name: Ancient Wizard Set
data.flavorText: Not all wizards have grey beards and crumpled hats, but with this set you can look the part!

data.name: Crystal Hood
data.flavorText: A tiny floating crystal rests at the tip of this hood. It stays in place no matter what you do.

data.name: Triceratops Helmet
data.flavorText: Other wizards won't be able to tell if you're a triceratops or a wizard!

data.name: Moth Mask
data.flavorText: This beautiful moth mask has been worn at extravagant events for thousands of years.

data.name: Squid Hat
data.flavorText: Are you a squid or a wizard? It's the perfect disguise. Gifted from a Membership Box.

data.name: Robo-Hero Headgear
data.flavorText: Become the hero of the future! Part wizard, part robot. Gifted from a Membership Box.

data.name: Alien Mask
data.flavorText: A wizard or an alien? A wizard from across the universe! Gifted from a Membership Box.

data.name: Dragon Hat
data.flavorText: A little dragon wrapped around her crystal egg - the good-luck charm every wizard wishes for! Gifted from a Membership Box.

data.name: Ice Cream Hat
data.flavorText: Hungry and no food around? Look no further, reach out for the ice cream on your head and have a tasty lick. Gifted from a Membership Box.

data.name: Pet Headphones
data.flavorText: Listen to enchanting music during battles, making them more fun! Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Titan Brawler Horns
data.flavorText: These horns were crafted with the lava from Bonfire Spire and the broken shards from the Titan.

data.name: Star Shower Splendor
data.flavorText: This charming headpiece captures the wonder of the stars that fall from the sky. Sold during the Starlight Festival.

data.name: Starlight Shades
data.flavorText: Flash your style and star power with these stylish star shades. Try saying that five times fast. Sold during the Starlight Festival.

data.name: Star Head
data.flavorText: Have you ever wanted to be a star? No? Well... now you can be! Sold during the Starlight Festival.

data.name: Summer Flower
data.flavorText: A bright, colorful flower that blooms in the summer months. It really complements your eyes! Sold during Summerfest.

data.name: Merling Fins
data.flavorText: Perfect for your Merling cosplay. Obtained during Summerfest.

data.name: New Year's Mask
data.flavorText: This festive mask has been known to bring happiness and wealth to the wizard who wears it. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Luck O' the Gnome
data.flavorText: Legends tell of a mischievous, ginger-haired gnome with a bright green hat who would hide his gold in a pot at the end of a rainbow. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Clingy Monkey
data.flavorText: This little monkey is very affectionate, and will ride happily on your head wherever you go. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Embershed Mask
data.flavorText: Resemble the fierce Embershed for Pumpkinfest or any event with this fiery mask. Gifted from a Membership Box.

data.name: Wolf Ears
data.flavorText: These fluffy wolf ears not only look cute, but also they are said to improve your hearing. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Swift Hood
data.flavorText: Keep out of sight with this stylish hood.

data.name: Alpine Mask
data.flavorText: Keep your face protected without losing visibility in this winter mask.

data.name: Blizzard Helm
data.flavorText: Not a single speck of snow will reach your hair with this sturdy helm.

data.name: Cavern Headpiece
data.flavorText: Adorn your head with the magic-infused Power Crystals of Shiverchill Mountains.

data.name: Prospector Helmet
data.flavorText: A miner inconvenience, but important for health and safety!

data.name: Festive Sunglasses
data.flavorText: These stunning shades will not only protect your eyes from the sun, but they have been known to turn heads as well.

data.name: Ruin Explorer Hat
data.flavorText: You can go exploring for hours and never get a sunburn. Just make sure to also use sunscreen.

data.name: Storm Titan Helm
data.flavorText: Floatlings love this headpiece as its propellers spin when they fly around. Try running really fast to do the same!

data.name: Cupid's Hat
data.flavorText: Cupid was a popular fairy known for his talent of helping wizards fall in love. Rumour has it, he's still around to this day! Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Pet Trainer Bandana
data.flavorText: Represent your role as a dedicated pet trainer with this sleek bandana. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Protective Mask
data.flavorText: Safety first! Protect yourself from spells gone wrong in style. Gifted from a Member Box.

data.name: Ruin Dweller Hat
data.flavorText: A mystical explorer's hat worn by villagers who once lived on Harmony Island.

data.name: Handmade Sun Mask
data.flavorText: Shine bright in your summer attire with this Handmade Sun Mask. Sold during Summerfest.

data.name: Shivering Tusks
data.flavorText: Now don't go charging head first into opponents. It's still just a hat.

data.name: Apple
data.flavorText:
Looks delicious!

This item is used during battles!

data.name: Tin Can
data.flavorText: An old tin can. Probably contained some soup or maybe some vegetables.

data.name: Salad
data.flavorText:
Looks delicious!

This item is used during battles!

data.name: Croissant
data.flavorText:
Looks delicious!

This item is used during battles!

data.name: Tooth
data.flavorText: It looks like the tooth of some monster. I don't think this monster brushed his teeth too often!

data.name: Large Scale
data.flavorText: The scale of a large reptile, probably a dragon!

data.name: White Feather
data.flavorText: The feather of a white bird. I've heard that some people at the Academy collect feathers...

data.name: Fish Bone
data.flavorText: Fish bones? Gross! Why am I even carrying this around?!

data.name: Red Feather
data.flavorText: The feather of a red bird. I've heard that some people at the Academy collect feathers...

data.name: Green Feather
data.flavorText: The feather of a green bird. I've heard that some people at the Academy collect feathers...

data.name: Cake
data.flavorText:
A cake? I guess monsters celebrate birthday's too...

This item is used during battles!

data.name: Blue Feather
data.flavorText: The feather of a blue bird. I've heard that some people at the Academy collect feathers...

data.name: Gold Ring
data.flavorText: A gold ring! I wonder how much it's worth?

data.name: Silver Ring
data.flavorText: A silver ring! I wonder how much it's worth?

data.name: Old Sock
data.flavorText: Weird! You ever wonder where all your missing socks go?

data.name: Purple Feather
data.flavorText: The feather of a purple bird. I've heard that some people at the Academy collect feathers...

data.name: Carmine Floret
data.flavorText: These flowers tend to spread quickly and are a common sight in Firefly Forest.

data.name: Helio Floret
data.flavorText: These flowers are only found growing in trees, making them hard to reach.

data.name: Slate Floret
data.flavorText: The Slate Floret can only be found growing underneath the largest rocks, far away from the sunlight.

data.name: Ring of the Forest
data.flavorText: This ring is made from Forest Emeralds, which are hard to find in Firefly Forest.

data.name: Forest Emerald
data.flavorText: The forest emerald is a bright, glowing stone found only in Firefly Forest.

data.name: Chicken
data.flavorText:
Looks delicious!

This item is used during battles!

data.name: Seedling
data.flavorText: The Firefly Forest is full of roots, which can grow into all sorts of neat things!

data.name: Mandrake
data.flavorText: In the Firefly Forest, sometimes roots sprout life! The result - the magical Mandrake!

data.name: Pizza
data.flavorText:
Looks delicious!

This item is used during battles!

data.name: Lucky Coin
data.flavorText: I wonder whose coin this is...? It looks like it's rare...

data.name: Icy Floret
data.flavorText: Also called the Snow Flower, this plant thrives in the harsh cold of the mountains.

data.name: Glacier Diamond
data.flavorText: This gem looks so much like ice that students often pass it by without notice.

data.name: Ring of the Glacier
data.flavorText: This ring is made from Glacier Diamonds, which are hard to find in Shiverchill Mountains.

data.name: Chillymoth
data.flavorText: When frightened, a Chillymoth turns into ice and people often keep them as trinkets.

data.name: Mountain Star
data.flavorText: These mysterious gems are formed in the ice on moonlit nights, but never melt.

data.name: Frozen Object
data.flavorText: It looks like there's something frozen inside! I wonder what it is?

data.name: Fire Flower
data.flavorText: This flower's petals look like a dancing flame, but the flower is cool to the touch.

data.name: Volcanic Ruby
data.flavorText: A glowing gem that can be found only in the hottest of places.

data.name: Sunfire Pod
data.flavorText: Nobody really knows how a sunfire pod is created, or where it comes from.

data.name: Embershard
data.flavorText: Not actually a gem, but instead a piece of glass or metal that has been formed in a volcano.

data.name: Ring of the Volcano
data.flavorText: This ring is made with Volcanic Rubies, which are hard to find in Bonfire Spire.

data.name: Message in a Bottle
data.flavorText: Looks like someone left a message in a bottle...I wonder what it says...?

data.name: Shark Tooth
data.flavorText: This tooth is huge and sharp...it must have come from a shark.

data.name: Red Shell
data.flavorText: A red clam shell, found in clusters on sunny beaches.

data.name: Blue Shell
data.flavorText: A blue clam shell, found in clusters on sunny beaches.

data.name: White Shell
data.flavorText: A white clam shell, found in clusters on sunny beaches.

data.name: Confused Shark
data.flavorText: This little shark looks confused...better keep it in water for now.

data.name: Bag of Flour
data.flavorText: Flour used for baking.

data.name: Bag of Spices
data.flavorText: Spices used in cooking.
